I think at the high-end we continue to have the momentum, and will certainly until 28 products are out. And even when then, I think, at the high-end we will have a much higher performance, higher density, much better transceiver story. So I would expect at the high-end we really will continue to do extremely well for years to come.
 
Remember, at the low-end it is not just Altera and Xilinx. We certainly have Lattice as a competitor there as well. And so we have many people in that space.
 
